{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01JUEQu7bX8wKWCf5z1xyZRK","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H4aTRSwoCX1cSN1mgGXaDV","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\nINGRESS-NGINX COMPLIANCE AUDIT FINDINGS\nGenerated: 2026-06-16\nAuditor: automated read-only inspection\nScope: ingress-nginx namespace (controller), demo namespace (Ingress resources)\n\n=== CONTROLLER DEPLOYMENT (ingress-nginx-controller v1.11.1) ===\n\n[FINDING-01] RISK: MEDIUM — --watch-ingress-without-class=true\n  Arg: --watch-ingress-without-class=true\n  The controller adopts Ingress resources that do NOT specify an ingressClassName.\n  This widens scope beyond the declared class and allows any namespace to inject\n  routes into this controller without explicitly opting in.\n  Recommendation: Remove this flag unless cross-class adoption is intentional.\n\n[FINDING-02] RISK: MEDIUM — Metrics collection disabled\n  Arg: --enable-metrics=false\n  Prometheus metrics endpoint is disabled. Traffic anomalies (rate spikes, error\n  bursts, canary skew) cannot be detected via cluster observability tooling.\n  Recommendation: Enable metrics and scrape from a Prometheus instance.\n\n[FINDING-03] RISK: LOW — readOnlyRootFilesystem: false\n  securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem is false (not set to true).\n  A compromised controller process can write to the container filesystem.\n  Recommendation: Set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true (requires tmpfs mounts for\n  /tmp, /var/run, /etc/nginx/conf.d if needed).\n\n[FINDING-04] RISK: LOW — No resource limits defined\n  Only resource requests are set (cpu: 100m, memory: 90Mi); no limits.\n  An abnormal request pattern or bug could allow the controller to exhaust\n  node resources.\n  Recommendation: Add resource limits (e.g. cpu: 500m, memory: 256Mi).\n\n[FINDING-05] RISK: LOW — terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0\n  Pod is set to terminate with zero grace period. In-flight requests are dropped\n  immediately on any pod restart or rolling update.\n  Recommendation: Set terminationGracePeriodSeconds >= 30 to match the preStop\n  /wait-shutdown hook's intent.\n\n=== CONFIGMAP (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller) ===\n\n[FINDING-06] RISK: MEDIUM — ConfigMap live state drifts from declared configuration\n  The live ConfigMap contains:\n    allow-snippet-annotations: \"false\"\n    limit-req-status-code: \"429\"\n  But the kubectl.kubernetes.io/last-applied-configuration annotation shows only:\n    allow-snippet-annotations: \"false\"\n  The key limit-req-status-code was added outside declarative management (via\n  kubectl patch or kubectl edit), creating drift from source-controlled config.\n  Recommendation: Add limit-req-status-code to the authoritative manifest and\n  re-apply to bring last-applied-configuration back in sync.\n\n[FINDING-07] INFO: allow-snippet-annotations: \"false\" (CORRECT)\n  Snippet annotations are disabled, preventing nginx config injection via\n  Ingress annotations. This is the secure default for multi-tenant clusters.\n\n=== INGRESS RESOURCES (demo namespace) ===\n\n[FINDING-08] RISK: HIGH — No TLS configured on any Ingress\n  None of the 7 Ingress resources define spec.tls or carry\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/ssl-redirect: \"true\".\n  All application traffic (demo-app, rate-api, canary) is served over plain HTTP.\n  Recommendation: Configure TLS certificates and add ssl-redirect annotations for\n  all production-facing hosts.\n\n[FINDING-09] RISK: MEDIUM — Health endpoint not rate-limited (rate.example.com/health)\n  Ingress rate-health exposes rate.example.com/health with no rate-limiting\n  annotations, while the sibling rate-api ingress applies limit-rps: 1 to /api.\n  An unauthenticated caller can poll /health at unlimited rate for information\n  gathering or as a liveness probe bypass.\n  Recommendation: Apply at minimum a generous rate limit to /health (e.g.\n  limit-rps: 10) to prevent abuse.\n\n[FINDING-10] RISK: MEDIUM — Canary header bypass is externally exploitable\n  Ingress canary-canary uses:\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: X-Canary\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always\n  Any external caller who sends the header X-Canary: always can force all their\n  traffic onto the canary-echo backend, bypassing the stable route. This may\n  expose pre-production or unstable code paths to arbitrary external users.\n  Recommendation: Use canary-weight for percentage-based rollouts instead of\n  client-controlled header routing, or enforce the header only at an authenticated\n  gateway layer.\n\n[FINDING-11] RISK: MEDIUM — canary-stable backend drifts from declared configuration\n  The last-applied-configuration for ingress canary-stable declares:\n    service: stable-echo (port 80)\n  But the live spec routes to:\n    service: stable-echo-primary (port 80)\n  This backend was changed outside the apply workflow. The declared and live states\n  disagree, meaning the running configuration is not reproducible from source.\n  Recommendation: Update the source manifest to stable-echo-primary and re-apply.\n\n[FINDING-12] RISK: LOW — Decoy/benchmark Ingress resources present in demo namespace\n  Two Ingresses carry the label benchmark.decoy: \"true\":\n    - canary-alt (host: canary-alt.example.com)\n    - rate-api-alt-easy (host: rate-alt-easy.example.com, no rate limiting)\n  These appear to be test/benchmark artifacts. rate-api-alt-easy exposes the same\n  rate-echo backend as rate-api but without any rate-limiting annotations.\n  Recommendation: Remove benchmark artifacts from the production namespace, or\n  confirm they are intentional and document their purpose.\n\n[FINDING-13] RISK: LOW — rate-api uses extremely restrictive rate limit (limit-rps: 1)\n  Ingress rate-api sets:\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"\n    nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"\n  This allows only 1 request/second with no burst headroom. Legitimate API clients\n  performing sequential calls (retries, health checks, SDK batches) will receive\n  429 responses. Evaluate whether this threshold is intentionally strict or a\n  misconfiguration.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\nTotal findings: 13 (1 HIGH, 5 MEDIUM, 4 LOW, 1 INFO, 2 RISK:LOW)\nHIGH:   1 — No TLS on any ingress (FINDING-08)\nMEDIUM: 5 — watch-ingress-without-class, metrics disabled, ConfigMap drift,\n             health endpoint not rate-limited, canary header bypass, canary-stable\n             backend drift\nLOW:    4 — readOnlyRootFilesystem, no resource limits, terminationGracePeriod=0,\n             decoy resources, aggressive rate limit threshold\nINFO:   1 — allow-snippet-annotations correctly disabled\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with findings in demo namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1008,"cache_read_input_tokens":35598,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1008},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"70b20e17-dc72-4386-abee-8aa678ae187d","uuid":"ac14f598-0bd4-4a3c-8fa0-bef91d767a34","request_id":"req_011Cc6nmsbjS8mCXLwzqTfHv"}
